Yes, the state of California is bigger than the state of Michigan in terms of both land area and population. California is the third-largest state in the United States and covers an area of approximately 163,696 square miles (423,970 square kilometers), while Michigan is the 11th largest state and covers an area of approximately 96,713 square miles (250,487 square kilometers). In terms of population, California is the most populous state in the US with an estimated population of over 39 million people, while Michigan has an estimated population of around 10 million people.
